{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d21b3eca-9a84-47e9-bdb0-e2fad1aeb726","content":"Yes, you'll have **compatibility issues** with your target frameworks. MSTest v3 drops support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is no longer supported; you need .NET 6+ (e.g., `net6.0`)\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework older than 4.6.2 is the minimum, so `net462` is the bare minimum and *may* work, but check the exact v3 requirements (some features require 4.7.2+)\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is dropped; you need `net6.0` or later\n\n**Summary of required changes:**\n\n| Current TFM | Issue | Replacement |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net5.0` | Dropped in v3 | `net6.0` or `net8.0` |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | Dropped in v3 | `net6.0` or `net8.0` |\n| `net462` | At the edge | `net462` (minimum) or `net472`+ recommended |\n\nWould you like me to run the full MSTest v2→v3 migration on this project? I can update the TFMs and packages for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4ca7e14a-46bd-49c7-82ea-719c2c32659a","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"EC02:527BE:667AED8:6EF1B07:6A034C1E"},"id":"1ff40a9c-e622-4ffa-9d42-81cb27e9b86b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:50:01.795Z","parentId":"8af0d145-240d-493d-a090-13ab8063669f"}
